NAME
     MoveX - move molecule in X direction

SYNOPSIS
     MoveX expr

DESCRIPTION
     Move all movable (set with DialMol) molecules by the
     given amount in X direction. Moving is normally done
     interactively by pressing the middle mouse button.
     This command is useful for being used in macros or
     for setting up the slider box.

EXAMPLE
     MoveX 10

SEE ALSO
     DialMol, DefPropMol, MoveY, MoveZ, MoveInit

